Build installer steps for Windows OS plataforms

Requeriments:
*NSIS (http://nsis.sourceforge.net/Download)
*Ruby (http://rubyinstaller.org/)
*Msys (http://sourceforge.net/projects/mingw/files/)

Procedure:
1) Install NSIS, Ruby and Msys
2) Set following environment variables (right click on My Computer, then Properties, Advanced, Environment variables):
On System variables section add the NSIS and Ruby bin folder to eviroment path variable. 
Example: ";C:\Program Files\NSIS;C:\Ruby\bin" (or whatever path you installed Ruby and NSIS)
2) run msys and cd to the installer source folder
3) ruby make-installer.rb
4) follow the instructions

ready!